2 Layered model
Editor Layer - For the user, contains information about the view, text, positions of gates, etc
Simulation Layer

# Editor Layer
Has positions of nodes, titles of nodes.
SkipNode - A node that doesnt exist, any gate getting this gates state actually just gets the state of the previous gate

# Simulation Layer
NodeKind
├── Constant              — no inputs, fixed output, never dirty
├── Nand                  — universal primitive
├── Identity              — explicit 1-tick delay (possibly just sugar for CombinationalLut)
├── CombinationalLut      — compiled acyclic subgraph, with a set delay - meaning we must store a queue of calculated ouputs
├── StatefulLut           — compiled cyclic subgraph, Map<(Input, InternalState), (Output, NextInternalState)>
├── Graph                 — nested simulation
└── External              — Editor passes in a function that decides how state is calculated



In simulation layer, but managed by editor layer sadly
pub enum ExternalNodeKind {
    Switch    { state: bool },
    UserInput { binding: InputBinding, current: bool },
    File      { data: Vec<u8> },
    Screen    { buffer: ScreenBuffer },
}

-- Avoid updating every node every tick
A node only needs updating If either an input changes or its internal state changes.

Store a list of "Dirty nodes".
Detect what wires changed, and then find out what gates need to be "dirty"/updated next frame.